---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Travel Nightmares: Visa Policies Impacting Fans and Referees" description="A deep dive into the cross-border logistical challenges of the 2026 tournament.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-[#F7803C]">
    <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl bg-white border-[4px] border-black p-8 md:p-12 shadow-[12px_12px_0px_#2E0D23] relative z-20">
      <div class="inline-block bg-yellow-300 text-black border-[3px] border-black font-black px-4 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">LOGISTICS</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-6 leading-none" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">
        Travel Nightmares: Visa Policies Impacting Fans and Referees
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-black font-medium leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-black border-l-8 border-l-blue-600">
          Hosting a massive tournament across three sovereign nations sounded like a huge W on paper. In reality? The visa and immigration logistics are becoming a massive headache for fans, staff, and even the teams themselves.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">1. The USA Visa Backlog</h2>
        <p>
          Currently, wait times for US visitor visas (B1/B2) in some countries are stretching over a year. If you wait until you secure match tickets to apply for your visa, you're going to take a massive L. FIFA is lobbying the US government to expedite the process for ticket holders, but do not rely on it. Get your paperwork sorted *yesterday*.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">2. Multi-Country Hop Headaches</h2>
        <p>
          Imagine this: Your team plays Match 1 in Toronto (Canada), Match 2 in Philadelphia (USA), and Match 3 in Monterrey (Mexico). You need legal clearance to enter *all three countries* within a 10-day span. That means multiple visas, multiple border checks, and massive potential for getting denied entry if your passport isn't strong.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">3. Referees and Staff Catching Strays</h2>
        <p>
          It isn't just fans. Support staff, media, and even referees from certain nations are facing massive bureaucratic hurdles to get cleared for cross-border travel during the knockout stages. The logistics are so insane that FIFA might literally have to assign referees based on their visa status rather than their skill level.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-between items-center border-t-[4px] border-black pt-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="font-outfit text-xl uppercase text-black hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">← Back to Guides</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
